# Development Workflow and Guidelines

This guide covers the development workflow, build process, and contribution guidelines for the Warden project.

## Development Environment
- **Xcode**: Version 14.3 or later required
- **macOS**: 13.0+ for development and testing
- **Swift**: Latest stable version
- **Target Platforms**: macOS 13.0+ (Intel and Apple Silicon)

## Project Configuration
- **Xcode Project**: [Warden.xcodeproj](mdc:Warden.xcodeproj) - Main Xcode project file
- **App Info**: [Info.plist](mdc:Warden/Info.plist) - App metadata and configuration
- **Entitlements**:  - App sandbox and capabilities
- **Code Formatting**: [.swift-format](mdc:Warden/.swift-format) - Swift formatting rules

## Build Process
- **Universal Binary**: Supports both Intel and Apple Silicon Macs
- **Notarization**: Apple notarized builds for distribution
- **Sparkle Integration**: Automatic update framework included
- **Asset Management**: [Assets.xcassets](mdc:Warden/Assets.xcassets) for app icons and images

## Code Quality
- **Swift Format**: Consistent code formatting with [.swift-format](mdc:Warden/.swift-format)
- **Architecture**: MVVM pattern with SwiftUI best practices
- **Documentation**: Inline documentation for public APIs
- **Testing**: Unit tests in [WardenTests](mdc:WardenTests) and UI tests in [WardenUITests](mdc:WardenUITests)

## Git Workflow
- **Main Branch**: Stable, release-ready code
- **Feature Branches**: Individual features and bug fixes
- **Commit Messages**: Clear, descriptive commit messages
- **Pull Requests**: Code review process for all changes

## Distribution
- **GitHub Releases**: Manual download of universal binaries
- **Homebrew**: `brew install --cask Warden` for package management
- **Build from Source**: Open source availability for custom builds

## Contribution Guidelines
- **Issues**: Check [Issues page](mdc:https:/github.com/Renset/macai/issues) before creating new ones
- **Unassigned Issues**: Pick any open, unassigned issue to work on
- **Code Style**: Follow existing patterns and Swift conventions
- **Testing**: Include tests for new features and bug fixes
- **Documentation**: Update relevant documentation for changes

## Key Dependencies
- **SwiftUI**: Primary UI framework
- **Core Data**: Local data persistence
- **Sparkle**: Automatic update framework
- **Foundation**: Core system frameworks

## Privacy and Security
- **Local Data**: All data stored locally, no cloud services
- **API Keys**: Secure storage and handling of user credentials
- **No Telemetry**: Zero data collection or usage tracking
- **Open Source**: Transparent development and security review

## Release Process
- **Version Bumping**: Update version numbers in project settings
- **Testing**: Comprehensive testing on multiple macOS versions
- **Notarization**: Apple notarization for security compliance
- **Distribution**: GitHub releases and Homebrew cask updates

